  <entry>
    <title>Getting Started with Platform Engineering</title>
    <link href="https://example.com/blog/getting-started-with-platform-engineering/"/>
    <updated>2024-11-15T00:00:00Z</updated>
    <id>https://example.com/blog/getting-started-with-platform-engineering/</id>
    <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;Platform engineeringhas become one of the hottest topics in the DevOps space, and for good reason. As organizations scale their engineering teams, the need for a solid internal developer platform (IDP) becomes increasingly critical.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What is Platform Engineering?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Platform engineering is the discipline of designing and building toolchains and workflows that enable self-service capabilities for software engineering teams. The goal is to reduce cognitive load on developers and increase their autonomy and velocity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Think of it as building products for your internal customers — the developers at your company.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Why Does It Matter?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Traditional DevOps often led to a &amp;quot;you build it, you run it&amp;quot; model that placed significant operational burden on development teams. Platform engineering aims to abstract away the complexity of infrastructure and operations, giving developers:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Self-service capabilities&lt;/strong&gt; — spin up environments, deploy services, and manage configurations without waiting for ops tickets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Golden paths&lt;/strong&gt; — opinionated, well-supported workflows that make the right thing the easy thing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Developer portals&lt;/strong&gt; — a single pane of glass for all developer tooling and documentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Getting Started&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you&#39;re looking to start building an internal developer platform, here are the key steps:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Talk to your developers&lt;/strong&gt; — understand their pain points and friction points&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Start small&lt;/strong&gt; — don&#39;t try to build everything at once; focus on the highest-impact workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Treat it as a product&lt;/strong&gt; — assign ownership, gather feedback, and iterate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Measure adoption&lt;/strong&gt; — track usage and developer satisfaction&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Useful Tools&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Some popular tools in the platform engineering space:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Backstage&lt;/strong&gt; — open-source developer portal from Spotify&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Crossplane&lt;/strong&gt; — infrastructure-as-code with Kubernetes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ArgoCD / Flux&lt;/strong&gt; — GitOps continuous delivery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Port&lt;/strong&gt; — internal developer portal&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Platform engineering is a journey, not a destination. Start with empathy for your users and iterate from there.&lt;/p&gt;
</content>
  </entry>
  <entry>
    <title>5 TypeScript Tips for Better Code Quality</title>
    <link href="https://example.com/blog/typescript-tips-for-better-code/"/>
    <updated>2024-09-03T00:00:00Z</updated>
    <id>https://example.com/blog/typescript-tips-for-better-code/</id>
    <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;After yearsof writing TypeScript, I&#39;ve collected a set of patterns that consistently improve code quality. Here are my top 5.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;1. Use &lt;code&gt;unknown&lt;/code&gt; Instead of &lt;code&gt;any&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When you don&#39;t know the type of something, reach for &lt;code&gt;unknown&lt;/code&gt; rather than &lt;code&gt;any&lt;/code&gt;. Unlike &lt;code&gt;any&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;unknown&lt;/code&gt; forces you to narrow the type before using it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;language-typescript&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-typescript&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token comment&quot;&gt;// Bad&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;token keyword&quot;&gt;function&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token function&quot;&gt;processData&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;data&lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token builtin&quot;&gt;any&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class=&quot;token keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; data&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;value&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token comment&quot;&gt;// No type checking!&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class=&quot;token comment&quot;&gt;// Good&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;token keyword&quot;&gt;function&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token function&quot;&gt;processData&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;data&lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token builtin&quot;&gt;unknown&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class=&quot;token keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token keyword&quot;&gt;typeof&lt;/span&gt; data &lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;===&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token string&quot;&gt;&#39;object&#39;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;&amp;amp;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; data &lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;!==&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;&amp;amp;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token string&quot;&gt;&#39;value&#39;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token keyword&quot;&gt;in&lt;/span&gt; data&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;span class=&quot;token keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; data&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;value&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token comment&quot;&gt;// Type-safe&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;2. Leverage Discriminated Unions&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Discriminated unions make pattern matching on types explicit and exhaustive.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;language-typescript&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-typescript&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token keyword&quot;&gt;type&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token class-name&quot;&gt;Result&lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token constant&quot;&gt;T&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;|&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt; status&lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token string&quot;&gt;&#39;success&#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt; data&lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token constant&quot;&gt;T&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;|&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt; status&lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token string&quot;&gt;&#39;error&#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt; message&lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token builtin&quot;&gt;string&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class=&quot;token keyword&quot;&gt;function&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token generic-function&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token function&quot;&gt;handleResult&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token generic class-name&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token constant&quot;&gt;T&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;result&lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; Result&lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token constant&quot;&gt;T&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class=&quot;token keyword&quot;&gt;switch&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;result&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;status&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;span class=&quot;token keyword&quot;&gt;case&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token string&quot;&gt;&#39;success&#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; result&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;data&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;span class=&quot;token keyword&quot;&gt;case&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token string&quot;&gt;&#39;error&#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token keyword&quot;&gt;throw&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token class-name&quot;&gt;Error&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;result&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;message&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;3. Use &lt;code&gt;satisfies&lt;/code&gt; for Type Validation Without Widening&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;satisfies&lt;/code&gt; operator lets you validate a value against a type without losing its specific type information.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;language-typescript&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-typescript&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token keyword&quot;&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; config &lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
  port&lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token number&quot;&gt;3000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;
  host&lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token string&quot;&gt;&#39;localhost&#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt; satisfies Record&lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token builtin&quot;&gt;string&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token builtin&quot;&gt;string&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;|&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token builtin&quot;&gt;number&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class=&quot;token comment&quot;&gt;// config.port is still typed as 3000, not number&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;4. Prefer Template Literal Types&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Template literal types are great for creating constrained string types.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;language-typescript&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-typescript&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token keyword&quot;&gt;type&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token class-name&quot;&gt;EventName&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token template-string&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token template-punctuation string&quot;&gt;`&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token string&quot;&gt;on&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token interpolation&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token interpolation-punctuation punctuation&quot;&gt;${&lt;/span&gt;Capitalize&lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token builtin&quot;&gt;string&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token interpolation-punctuation punctuation&quot;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token template-punctuation string&quot;&gt;`&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;token keyword&quot;&gt;type&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token class-name&quot;&gt;HttpMethod&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token string&quot;&gt;&#39;GET&#39;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;|&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token string&quot;&gt;&#39;POST&#39;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;|&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token string&quot;&gt;&#39;PUT&#39;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;|&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token string&quot;&gt;&#39;DELETE&#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;token keyword&quot;&gt;type&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token class-name&quot;&gt;ApiRoute&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token template-string&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token template-punctuation string&quot;&gt;`&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token string&quot;&gt;/api/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token interpolation&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token interpolation-punctuation punctuation&quot;&gt;${&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token builtin&quot;&gt;string&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token interpolation-punctuation punctuation&quot;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token template-punctuation string&quot;&gt;`&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;5. Use &lt;code&gt;const&lt;/code&gt; Assertions&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;as const&lt;/code&gt; turns mutable objects into readonly tuples and narrows their types to literals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;language-typescript&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-typescript&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token keyword&quot;&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token constant&quot;&gt;DIRECTIONS&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token string&quot;&gt;&#39;north&#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token string&quot;&gt;&#39;south&#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token string&quot;&gt;&#39;east&#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token string&quot;&gt;&#39;west&#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token keyword&quot;&gt;as&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token keyword&quot;&gt;const&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;token keyword&quot;&gt;type&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token class-name&quot;&gt;Direction&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token keyword&quot;&gt;typeof&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token constant&quot;&gt;DIRECTIONS&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token builtin&quot;&gt;number&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token comment&quot;&gt;// &#39;north&#39; | &#39;south&#39; | &#39;east&#39; | &#39;west&#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These patterns have saved me countless hours of debugging. Try incorporating them into your next TypeScript project!&lt;/p&gt;
</content>
